<div id="review_967087688" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/967087688" />
    <a title="Niles" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/21044979-niles"><img alt="Niles" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1373931584p2/21044979.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/967087688?book_show_action=true">Jun 14, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Niles" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Niles" href="/user/show/21044979-niles">Niles</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780984755707" href="/book/show/13184491-avogadro-corp">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer967087688" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3682312664771551561">Avogadro corporation is the world&apos;s largest Internet service provider with a wide range of services. David Ryan is a computer programmer hired to make improvements to the company&apos;s e-mail program. The program David came up with was named ELOPe.<br/>Much as the spell checker and grammar checker programs available now, ELOPe would analyze previous e-mails and make suggestions on wording to provide the optimal result. The problem was that ELOPe analyzed ALL the e-mails written and thus used a lot of com</span>
  <span id="freeText3682312664771551561" style="display:none">Avogadro corporation is the world's largest Internet service provider with a wide range of services. David Ryan is a computer programmer hired to make improvements to the company's e-mail program. The program David came up with was named ELOPe.<br />Much as the spell checker and grammar checker programs available now, ELOPe would analyze previous e-mails and make suggestions on wording to provide the optimal result. The problem was that ELOPe analyzed ALL the e-mails written and thus used a lot of computing power. More and more servers were required to keep ELOPe running, and it was still in the testing stage.<br />Gary Mitchell, head of the communications division, gave David a deadline of one week to streamline the program so it would not require a massive amount of servers to run it. If David could not do it, then Gary would pull the servers away from ELOPe and put them to work on finished products actually making money.<br />Try as he might, David was not able to reduce the computing power required without compromising the efficiency of the program. The night before the deadline, David inserted code into the program directing it to do everything possible to insure the success of the ELOPe program. Unknown to David at the time, that action gave birth to an artificial intelligence.<br />Fearing that the ELOPe AI would take away man's free will, David and his team tried to wipe the program from the internet and the servers involved.<br />A thought provoking story, I thoroughly enjoyed the book. As an aside, a computer in England recently passed the Turing test, the benchmark established to determine if a computer is capable of human-like thought. This book may be fiction now, but soon it may become fact.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3682312664771551561" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


